<TITLE> 5 killed as bus caught fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bandarban, Jan 8 (bdnews24.com)  At least five people were killed and another 45 injured in Bandarban on Friday when a picnic bus caught fire and plunged into a roadside ditch. The dead passengers have been identified as Rupak Barua, Shova Barua, 35, Prakash Badi Barua, 35, Happy Barua, 32, and Patu Barua, 70. Witnesses said the bus caught fire in the Manur Tek area of Bandarban-Keranihat road and then fell into the roadside ditch at around 11.30 am. Pulak Barua, a passenger of the bus, told bdnews24.com that all the passengers were residents of Chittagong's Jobra village. Five with severe burn injuries were admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. Bandarban Sadar thana sub inspector Rafiq Islam said that fire fighters and police reached the spot in short time and rescued the passengers. bdnews24
